Story of My BookAfter a series of traumatic concussions, the direction of my life was forever altered. I Need a Walk explores my personal journey of healing, by way of backpacking the length of New Zealand’s South Island.My name is Claire Lewinski and I am the author of I Need A Walk. I wrote this book because I felt unseen and misunderstood after my brain injuries. I’m hoping my story can help others feel validated and show the possibility of resiliency.My hope is that, in reading this book, you will discover the truth behind living with a brain injury and the difficult process of recovery. I want you to see this book as inspiration and an opportunity to overcome hardship, escape from personal lock down, and learn alongside me about the importance of healing, in your own way. In this book, you will encounter multifaceted dimensions of identity and adventure through narratives like:
How my concussions severely impacted my well-being — challenging how I defined myself when I could no longer work, go to school, exercise, or even communicate in the same way; 
How subtle impacts and slip ups, caused by my brain injuries, severely impacted my decision making skills leading me question my ability to live independently;
Overcoming the natural challenges faced hiking through the Southern Alps, including river crossings, cyclones, and uncontrollable diarrhea, as well as the incredible moments of silence in the mountains, filtering through the light of the rising sun. 
You will love this book if you are passionate about mental health, feel a connection with nature, and like a good adventure. I Need a Walk speaks to people coming of age and survivors who want to grapple with finding themselves and healing from trauma in a new way.Ultimately, I hope that I Need a Walk inspires reflection and fruitful dialogue, pressing into engaging questions like:
How are you seizing your struggle?
How do you define personal success?
Why is mental health a luxury?
I look forward to exploring these questions and beyond with my readers. I believe discussing mental health, recovery, and exploration will change us all for the better.  The Book - I Need A Walk
The book is written in four parts.Part 1 Reward  to Resting. As a young adult, I’m just trying to find my place in the world. I discuss how my life began to unravel as I tried to navigate a concussion. I was forced to realize how serious the injury was and start making adjustments in my life. Part 2 Finding the Sun to Entering the New. One concussion turned out to be three separate concussions, leading to a traumatic brain injury diagnosis and long lasting impacts. I took my recovery seriously, going through therapy and continuing on with life, learning the value of a supportive community and advocating for myself. Part 3 The Beginning to Hike Your Own Hike. I found a way to continue my recovery by backpacking over 800 miles, the length of the South Island of New Zealand, with a dear friend. I continued to struggle with my head, but found the space to really start healing. As I climbed mountains, experienced trail magic and unexpected challenges, I regained my sense of identity and confidence, realizing the unstoppable power of a human being. Part 4 is an afterword, glancing into my life after the walk and how I’ve continued to heal, thrive, and find my own way.  What I Need & What You'll GetThis book will be published with New Degree Press. I set up the pre-order tiers to help cover the costs for publishing my book. Money raised will go towards the following:The editor I will work with to revise and publish my manuscript in August, 2021. 
The cover design of my book; (The mockups you see currently are a placeholder!)
The layout design for the interior of my book (physical copy, ebook formats);
The copy editing for my book to polish the grammar and spelling prior to publication;
The launch & promotion efforts for my book when I ultimately publish this summer.
When I pre-sell 120 copies of my book, I will publish a paperback and ebook. When I pre-sell 150 copies of my book, I will also publish a hardcover edition. When I pre-sell 200 copies of my book, I will publish a hardcover and an audiobook.I am also offering some exclusive rewards for people who pre-order my book now:
You will receive a personally signed copy of my book when I publish;
Your name will appear in the Acknowledgments;
You will receive early access to the Author’s Note and other excerpts from my book, with the opportunity to review it and give me early feedback;
You will have the opportunity to be involved in selecting my cover and title;
You will be invited to join my Author Community and get behind-the-scenes sneak peeks into the publishing process;
And much more!
 About the AuthorClaire Lewinski is finishing her chemical engineering degree remotely from New Zealand. She has had the opportunity to advocate for issues she’s passionate about including sexual violence, science policy, and conservation. She decided to share her story in hopes that brain injuries will become less stigmatized. Ultimately, helping others overcome hardship. Claire is always up for an adventure and tries to go backpacking whenever she can get a few days off. Recently, she’s become obsessed with Brazilian Jiu Jitsu as she notices it continues to help with her recovery. She is fueled by dark chocolate and bad jokes. For more information, you can connect with Claire at clairelewinski.4@gmail.com, or connect through LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/claire-lewinski-231..., Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/claire.lewi8, or Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/claire_lewi/.  International Preorders For international preorders outside of the United States or New Zealand, please send me a private message. Shipping is included for those in the United States and New Zealand.  Risks & ChallengesThe biggest challenge with publishing a book is delivering the finished book to the backer, specifically my mailing of the book to you. I have eliminated this risk by including the cost of mailing and shipping the signed copies into each pre-order tier. The risk of delivering the pre-sale copies of my book is contingent on the publisher we use. I will be working closely with New Degree Press to make sure we ship the pre-order rewards to you as early as possible. We will keep all pre-sale backers up-to-date as to when my book will publish. You will know when the copies of my book you pre-ordered are expected to ship. Other Ways You Can HelpSome people just can't contribute, but that doesn't mean they can't help:
Please share my pre-sale campaign on Facebook, Twitter, and LinkedIn with your friends, family and network. Please use #ineedawalk and tag me as well as my publisher, New Degree Press, so we can help amplify your efforts.
You can easily share my Pre-Sale Campaign Page via Indiegogo at the top of the page.
Please share my book with 5 friends, family members, or co-workers who you think would enjoy it via text or direct message on social media.
 Thank you so much for of all of your love and support!Thanks again,Claire Lewinski
